DERIVING THE FORMULA (Level 1 structure)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  1/alpha_EM = (5/3)/alpha_1 + 1/alpha_2
            = (8/3)/alpha_2 + (5/3)*(1/alpha_1 - 1/alpha_2)

  sin^2(theta_W) = (1/alpha_2) / (1/alpha_EM)
                 = 3/8 - (5/8) * (inv_a1 - inv_a2) / alpha_inv

  This is EXACT in Fraction arithmetic.
  No one-loop approximation is needed for the formula itself.
  The one-loop approximation enters only in determining
  WHERE inv_a1 and inv_a2 come from (running from M_GUT).

  sin^2(theta_W) direct (dimensionless)    0.23122
  sin^2(theta_W) measured (dimensionless)  0.23122

VERIFICATION: FORMULA IS AN IDENTITY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  The formula sin^2 = 3/8 - (5/8)*(inv_a1 - inv_a2)/alpha_inv
  is an algebraic identity equivalent to the DEFINITION of
  the GUT-normalized couplings. It reproduces the input
  sin^2(theta_W) exactly:

